## 4. Risks + mitigations

| Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |
|---|---|---|
| Stage B produces different assignments than current (regression) | Medium | Config-flag gate + parallel runs on validation scope with tolerance-based diff |
| Stage B infeasibility for resources over-booked in Stage A | Low-medium | Slack vars in Stage B; report as PARTIAL |
| LC-05 weekend coupling interaction splits across stages awkwardly | Medium | Keep LC-05 free-weekend vars in Stage A (since they depend on demand presence), export selected ones to Stage B |
| Priority-1 anchor state management complicates Stage B | Low | Single pass means the anchor fires cleanly for the first day of plan range; no inter-partition propagation |
| Performance regression at very large scope (1000+ resources) | Low | Stage B is small model, likely faster than current partitioned total |
| Breaks existing test suite | Medium | Keep legacy path behind flag; run test suite against both until confidence built |

