## 5. When to actually build this

**Do NOT build this if:**
- Current architecture continues to pass all validation (R7+ reports).
- No new LC-06 bug class emerges.
- Production is stable with Fix #14+#15.

**DO build this if:**
- A regression appears that can't be cleanly traced to Fix #14 or #15's
  scope — i.e., the partitioned approach starts failing in new ways.
- Product requirements change such that LC-06 needs to support new
  semantics (weekly rest minimums? cross-month smoothing? different
  proration rules?).
- We want to parallelize partition solves for throughput.
- Phase I carryover state handling becomes a maintenance burden (today it's
  stable; may not be true forever).

**Intermediate option if the above isn't quite enough pressure:**
- Refactor LC-06 into its own module that LOOKS like Stage B (same public
  API) but today runs per-partition. Makes the future rewrite easier
  without requiring a full switch today.

